At 09:52 AM 9/13/2002 -0400, Rich wrote:
>I have a 71 camper (Lift from the rear) with a cot on top.  Is there any 
>way to switch tops to put on a "Front Lift" so i can install a double bed 
>on this?

Westfalia used buses with a special flat roof for their late bay 
conversions.  You would have to
cut your roof off, and weld a donor roof in its place.

Have you considered an AVI/Riviera straight-up pop top?  These will work on 
early bays, as they
were installed on them.

